      <scopecontent id="aspace_225dcc0c2f1dd7f2ac606980e463c5d4">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The J.O.Wright and Company records consist of approximately two hundred letters, bills, and receipts addressed to James Osborne Wright, Robert Fridenberg, and others, concerning orders for prints and engravings imported by J. O. Wright and Company of New York City. The materials have been arranged in alphabetical order, and an index to correspondents may be found at the end of this register. Also among the papers is an annotated catalogue, The Engraved Portraits of Washington, which ocntains laid-in notes and printed matter.</p>
         <p>These papers were donated to Yale University in 1956 by J. V. Reed.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
